// E2E tests for unary message sends
// Unary messages are single-word messages with no arguments
//
// NOTE: Many unary methods (negated, abs, isZero, isEven, isOdd, etc.) are
// defined in the stdlib but use conditional logic (ifTrue:ifFalse:) which
// currently returns futures in the REPL. These are documented in lib/*.bt
// but full E2E testing awaits synchronous evaluation support.
//
// The tests below verify unary message syntax with built-in block evaluation.

// ===========================================================================
// BLOCK UNARY MESSAGES (verified working)
// ===========================================================================

// Block value (unary message to block)
[42] value
// => 42

// Block value with computed body
[10 + 5] value
// => 15

// Nested block value
[[3] value + 2] value
// => 5

